description: This table contains implant information that changes over time.

columns.name: IMPLANT_ID
columns.description: The unique identifier for the implant record.

columns.name: CONTACT_DATE_REAL
columns.description: A unique contact date in decimal format. The integer portion of the number indicates the date of contact. The digits after the decimal distinguish different contacts on the same date and are unique for each contact on that date. For example, .00 is the first/only contact, .01 is the second contact, etc.

columns.name: CONTACT_DATE
columns.description: The date of this contact in calendar format.

columns.name: CONTACT_NUMBER
columns.description: The contact number of the implant record.

columns.name: CM_CT_OWNER_ID
columns.description: The Community ID (CID) of the instance that owns this contact. This is only populated if you use IntraConnect.

columns.name: LINKED_ORDER_ID
columns.description: A link to the order record with relevant information for the implant on a contact (e.g. the interrogation report for a pacemaker).

columns.name: ICD_HIGH_VOLT_OHMS
columns.description: The high voltage impedance of the ICD in Ohms.

columns.name: CNCT_LOG_ID
columns.description: The log where this specific contact on the implant was used. For example, if an implant was implanted in log 100, this will contain the value 100 for that contact. If it is then adjusted in another log, that contact will point to that log.

columns.name: ICD_BATT_VOLT_V
columns.description: Records the battery voltage of a generator in volts.

columns.name: PACE_FAST_VT_RATE
columns.description: The Fast VT detection rate of an implanted pacemaker.

columns.name: LEAD_SHOCK_OHM
columns.description: The shock impedance of the lead in Ohms.

columns.name: CNCT_SURGERY_CSN_ID
columns.description: The Contact Serial Number (CSN) of the log where this specific contact on the implant was used. For example, if an implant was implanted in log 100 having CSN 120, this will contain the value 120 for that contact. If it is then adjusted in another log, that contact will point to the CSN of that log.

columns.name: PAT_ENC_CSN_ID
columns.description: This item stores the Contact Serial Number (CSN) of the patient encounter where this specific contact on the implant was created. For example, for an implant was edited in an office visit encounter with CSN 120, this item will contain a value of 120 for that contact.
